definition.value: A 1,3-oxazole having benzyl, hydroxymethylene and oxo groups at positions 2, 4 and 5 respectively.
A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazoline-2,4(1H,3H)-dione which is substituted at position 3 by a 2-[4-(p-fluorobenzoyl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl group.

An organophosphate oxoanion that is the trianion of beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcA-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Glc-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glc-1-diphospho-ditrans,polycis-undecaprenol arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups and the carboxy group of the glucuronic acid residue; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by removal of the proton from the phosphate group of L-seryl-AMP.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which the amine function has formed an amide with a fatty acid RCO2H.
A carboxamide derivative between one or more of the nitrogens of spermidine and a hydroxycinnamic acid.
Any C18 straight-chain fatty acid having two C#C triple bonds.
A glycopentaosylceramide having alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the pentasaccharide component.
A piperidinium ion resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen atom of flavoxate.
A member of the class of flavones that is flavone substituted at position 3 by a methyl group and at position 8 by a carboxylic acid group.
A member of the class of piperidine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen atom is substituted by a 2-hydroxyethyl group.
An acrylic polymer, composed of poly(butyl 2-cyanoacrylate) macromolecules.
A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide that is a disaccharide consisting of two glucose residues linked via a diphospho group to undecaprenol.
An acrylic polymer, composed of poly(spiropyran methacrylate) macromolecules.
An acrylic polymer, composed of poly[N-2-(hydroxypropyl) methacrylamide] macromolecules.
A beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-D-GalNAc having beta-configuration at the reducing end anomeric centre.
An acrylic polymer, composed of poly(glycerol 1-O-monomethacrylate) macromolecules.
An acrylic polymer, composed of poly(ethoxyethyl acrylate) macromolecules.

An amino disaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose linked via a (1->3)-glycosidic bond to N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine. beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc in which the configuration at the reducing-end anomeric centre is beta.

An organophosphate oxoanion that is the dianion of beta-D-Glc-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glc-1-diphospho-ditrans,polycis-undecaprenol arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.

A galactosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of alpha-D-galactose and, by extension, of a lower oligosaccharide having alpha-D-galactose at the reducing end. The unsubstituted parent of the class of alpha-D-galactosyl groups.
A flavonoid oxoanion that is the conjugate base of hesperetin arising from selective deprtotonation of the 7-hydroxy group.
A ciguatoxin comprising a linear sequence of ten trans-fused five-, six-, eight- and nine-membered rings.
A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide that is a trisaccharide consisting of one mannose and two glucose residues linked via a diphospho group to undecaprenol.

An organophosphate oxoanion that is the dianion of alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Glc-(1->4)-alpha-D-Glc-1-diphospho-ditrans,polycis-undecaprenol arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A polyprenyl glucosyl phosphate in which a glucosyl residue is linked to a undecaprenyl group via a diphospho group.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the dianion of alpha-D-glucosyl ditrans,polycis-undecaprenyl diphosphate arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A polycyclic ether comprising a linear sequence of sequence of five trans-fused oxacycles and one spiro-fused tetrahydrofuran ring.
A poly(ethoxy ethylacrylate) polymer, composed of poly(2-ethoxyethyl acrylate) macromolecules.
A poly(ethoxyethyl acrylate) polymer, composed of poly(1-ethoxyethyl acrylate) macromolecules.
A nickel-iron-sulfur cluster in which the nickel and iron atoms are linked by bridging sulfur atoms in a cubane-type structure with the ratio Ni:Fe:S = 1:3:4.
An acrylic polymer, composed of poly(2-ethylhexyl methacrylate) macromolecules.
An acrylic polymer, composed of poly[2-(dimethylamino)ethyl methacrylate] macromolecules.
A polycyclic ether comprising a linear sequence of sequence of four trans-fused oxacycles and one spiro-fused tetrahydrofuran ring.
The cation resulting from the protonation of the imidazole group of butaconazole.
Arabinofuranosyl groups which are arabinan side chains of pectin composed of alpha-(1->5)-linked Araf residues, and which can be further branched by alpha-L-Araf units at O-2 and/or O-3.
A deoxyribonucleotide residue in which a 5-hydroxymethyluracil residue is glycosidically linked via the 5-hydroxymethyl oxygen to beta-D-glucose.

Hemicelluloses are polysaccharides in plant cell walls that have beta-(1->4)-linked backbones with an equatorial configuration. Hemicelluloses include xyloglucans, xylans, mannans and glucomannans, and beta-(1->3,1->4)-glucans.
An anthranilate obtained by removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of 5-nitroanthranilic acid.
A monohydroxybenzoate that is obtained by removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of 5-nitrosalicylic acid.
The ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of scopolamine.
A polycyclic ether comprising a linear sequence of sequence of six trans-fused oxacycles and one spiro-fused tetrahydrofuran ring.
A hydrobromide that is obtained by reaction of scopolamine with hydrogen bromide.
A hydrate that is the trihydrate form of scopolamine hydrobromide.
A polycyclic ether comprising a linear sequence of sequence of five trans-fused oxacycles and one spiro-fused tetrahydrofuran ring.
A polycyclic ether comprising a linear sequence of sequence of six trans-fused six-, seven- and eight-membered oxacycles.

Ciguatoxins are cyclic polyether toxins, derived from marine dinoflagellates, which are responsible for the symptoms of ciguatera poisoning. Ingestion of tropical and subtropical fin fish contaminated by ciguatoxins results in an illness characterised by neurological, cardiovascular and gastrointestinal disorders.
A quaternary ammonium salt resulting from the reaction of the amino group of scopolamine with methyl bromide.
A ciguatoxin comprising a sequence of twelve trans-fused six-, seven-, eight- and nine-membered oxacycles and a spiro-fused tetrahydrofuran.
